    "client_msg_id": "011e5f32-6b98-4070-98c2-a5d8645844ec",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Abstractly, you can have all kinds of things going on.  Yes, any command will have more or less syntax and the output will appear as more or less as structured text, but that doesn't mean that the output *is* text.  For example, just behind this Slack window, I have Pry running <https://github.com/pry/pry>.  The command language is Ruby (text), but the output made of Ruby objects.  Yes, they get printed, but I can do more stuff with them than the output of a UNIX shell command.",
